## Context

After all subdirectory aliases exist, add higher-level grouped aliases to make common workflows fast.

## Aliases to Add

```elixir
# Inner loop: the core agent/session/event stack
"test.core" => ["ecto.create --quiet", "ecto.migrate --quiet",
  "test test/pag_server/agents/ test/pag_server/sessions/ test/pag_server/events/ test/pag_server/context/"],

# LLM + integration provider stack
"test.provider" => ["ecto.create --quiet", "ecto.migrate --quiet",
  "test test/pag_server/llm/ test/pag_server/integrations/"],

# Infrastructure layer
"test.infra" => ["ecto.create --quiet", "ecto.migrate --quiet",
  "test test/pag_server/containers/ test/pag_server/cluster/ test/pag_server/cache/ test/pag_server/auth/ test/pag_server/security/"],

# Exclude slow/external tests (run the bulk of fast tests)
"test.fast" => ["ecto.create --quiet", "ecto.migrate --quiet",
  "test --exclude slow --exclude integration --exclude docker --exclude docker_required --exclude requires_anthropic --exclude requires_groq --exclude requires_zai --exclude requires_ollama --exclude requires_openrouter --exclude pgvector --exclude flaky"],
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `mix test.core` runs agents + sessions + events + context tests
- [ ] `mix test.provider` runs llm + integrations tests
- [ ] `mix test.infra` runs containers + cluster + cache + auth + security tests
- [ ] `mix test.fast` runs full suite excluding all tagged slow/external tests
